  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (427c1b5 2022-12-07T00:03:33.121971646Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil --load-state\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nNone\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nHello, the `--load-state` flag on the anvil CLI seems broken. Here are the stepx to reproduce:\r\n\r\n1. Run `anvil --state ./state.json` with state.json not existing\r\n2. Run `forge script script/script.s.sol --tc PocScript --fork-url http://localhost:8545 --broadcast` (script is given below)\r\n3. Notice that `cast call <deployed_address> \"a()(uint256)` correctly returns `1`\r\n4. `CTRL+C` anvil (state is correctly outputed in state.json)\r\n5. Re-run `anvil --state ./state.json`\r\n6. Notice that `cast call <deployed_address> \"a()(uint256)` correctly returns `1`, confirming the state has been loaded from state.json\r\n7. `CTRL+C` anvil\r\n8. Run `anvil --load-state ./state.json`\r\n9. Notice that `cast call <deployed_address> \"a()(uint256)` throws `Contract <deployed_address> does not exist`\r\n\r\nHere is the script used:\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.17;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Poc {\r\n    uint256 public a;\r\n\r\n    constructor(uint256 _a) {\r\n        a = _a;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract PocScript is Script {\r\n    function run() public {\r\n        uint256 DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY = vm.envUint(\"DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY\");\r\n\r\n        vm.startBroadcast(DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY);\r\n        Poc poc = new Poc(1);\r\n        vm.stopBroadcast();\r\n\r\n        console.log(\"Deployed at:\", address(poc));\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
